Package parser.nodes

This package contains numerous packages and classes that are used during the compilation and execution of a program. The classes in this package are the BaseNode (contains all of the code to be executed). EmptyNode (represents an empty line in the program). EvaluateNode (evaluates a given statement during execution). PrintNode (prints all print statements in the program).
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    BaseNode
    This class contains a lost of all the statements in the program and will sequentially execute them.
    EmptyNode
    Literally an empty statement.
    EvaluateNode
    Evaluate and return a number
    PrintNode
    Class that is used to create a print statement.
